:It can be viewed as the Lie algebra of 3×3 strictly upper-triangular matrices, with the commutator Lie bracket and the basis
::formula_233

:Over the real numbers, formula_234 is the Lie algebra of the Heisenberg group formula_235, that is, the group of matrices
::formula_236
:under matrix multiplication.

:For any field &quot;F&quot;, the center of formula_230 is the 1-dimensional ideal formula_238, and the quotient formula_239 is abelian, isomorphic to formula_240. In the terminology below, it follows that formula_230 is nilpotent (though not abelian).

* The Lie algebra formula_242 of the rotation group SO(3) is the space of skew-symmetric 3 x 3 matrices over formula_130. A basis is given by the three matrices
::formula_244
:The commutation relations among these generators are
